                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18171203-119-off621 t18171203-119-crimeloc624"></join>. On the 1st of December, about ten o'clock, I was in the back room, and saw the prisoner go out of the shop with the coat. I ran out - He was stopped, and brought back with it.</p>
               <p>HARRIET SIMPSON. I live in Crown-street. I saw a man looking in at Newbold's window; he opened the shop-door - I saw the prisoner run out, I pursued and stopped him; he threw the coat down.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
